data.chText: （乘公共汽车、火车、汽车等）上下班往返，经常往返（于两地）
data.enText: to travel regularly by bus, train, car, etc. between your place of work and your home

data.chText: 她每天上下班往返于牛津与伦敦之间。
data.enText: She commutes from Oxford to London every day.

data.chText: 那年他穿梭来往于纽约与芝加哥之间。
data.enText: He spent that year commuting between New York and Chicago.

data.chText: 我住在离都柏林上下班可乘公交车往返的地方。
data.enText: I live within commuting distance of Dublin.

data.chText: 亟须得到工作的人会愿意长途乘车往返上下班。
data.enText: People are prepared to commute long distances if they are desperate for work.
to replace one punishment with another that is less severe
to exchange one form of payment, for sth else
the journey that a person makes when they commute to work

data.chText: 去华盛顿中心区两小时的上下班路程
data.enText: a two-hour commute into downtown Washington
I have only a short commute to work.

simple_means.memory_skill: com 共同 + mut 改变，交换 + e → 共同换乘 → 选择公共交通上下班

means: (乘公共汽车、火车、汽车等)上下班往返，经常往返(于两地)

tr: a regular journey of some distance to and from your place of work
example: there is standing room only on the high-speed commute

tr: exchange or replace with another, usually of the same kind or category
example: Could you convert my dollars into pounds?

tr: exchange a penalty for a less severe one
change the order or arrangement of
example: Dyslexics often transpose letters in a word

tr: exchange positions without a change in value
example: These operators commute with each other

tr: travel back and forth regularly, as between one's place of work and home

value.def: If you commute, you travel a long distance every day between your home and your place of work.

example.ex: Mike commutes to London every day...
example.tran: 迈克每天都去伦敦上班。

example.ex: McLaren began commuting between Paris and London...
example.tran: 麦克拉伦开始往返于巴黎与伦敦之间。
他打算乘长途车往返上下班。

value.tran: (经很远的路程)上下班往返;通勤

example.ex: The number of commuters to London has dropped by 100,000.
example.tran: 往返于伦敦的上班族减少了10万。

value.def: A commute is the journey that you make when you commute.

example.ex: The average Los Angeles commute is over 60 miles a day.
example.tran: 洛杉矶的平均上下班路程为每天60多英里。

value.def: If a death sentence or prison sentence is commuted to a less serious punishment, it is changed to that punishment.

example.ex: His death sentence was commuted to life imprisonment...
example.tran: 他的死刑被减为无期徒刑。

rootsaffixes.indicate: = to change 改变, 交换
rootsaffixes.title: mut

partsOfSpeech.d: 交换；选择公共交通上下班

mut 改变，交换 + able 可…的，能…的；具有…性质的 → 能变的 → 易变的

muti〔= mut〕改变，交换 + nous → 容易变的 → 叛乱的
mut 改变，交换 + iny → 叛乱，兵变
mut 改变，交换 + ual 有…性质的 → 一起变的 → 相互的
per 贯穿 + mut 改变，交换 + e → 全部变 → 改变…次序
trans 变换 + mut 改变，交换 + e → 产生变化 → 使变形
